:R-HSA-1483166  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006654 ;
        rdfs:comment        "In the de novo synthesis of phosphatidic acid (PA), lysophosphatidic acid (LPA) is initially formed by the esterification of sn-1 by glycerol 3-phosphate acyltransferase (GPAT) from glycerol 3-phosphate (G3P). Next, LPA is converted to PA by a LPA acyltransferase (AGPAT, also known as LPAAT). In addition to this, PA is also formed when phosphatidylcholine (PC) is hydrolyzed by phospholipases D1 and D2 (PLD1 and 2). PA is involved in acyl chain remodeling via cleavage by phospholipases followed by reacylation by acyltransferases (Ghomashchi et al. 2010, Singer et al. 2002, Prasad et al. 2011, Shindou & Shimizu 2009, Cao et al. 2006)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Synthesis of PA" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Williams, MG, 2011-09-14" , "Reviewed: Wakelam, Michael, 2012-05-14" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Williams, MG, 2011-08-12" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-1483166" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-1483206/R-HSA-1483206> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

